data.title: Portrait of John, King of England
data.meta_description: Portrait of John, King of England. Born 24 December 1166 in Oxford, England. Died 19 October 1216 in Newark-on-Trent, England. Steel engraving, and Stipple engraving, c. 1850. Reasonable. Paper slightly soiled, with a faint stain in the lower right corner. Verso: blank. Dimensions: 203 x 153 mm. John, King of England was King, King of England, Lord of Ireland, Member of the House of Plantagenet, and "John Lackland".
